Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.67,0:00:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Till now, during this whole day, I’ve had the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.36,0:00:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then again, what's the difference between a world where left and right is reversed, and one that's been flipped around?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.82,0:00:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of me still thinks they're the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.71,0:00:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Regarding the scenery, that might very well be the case, but not with people's personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.48,0:00:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanekawa Tsubasa's example would no doubt be the simplest to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.44,0:00:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The oddity in question, which appeared during golden week ー
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.37,0:00:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,While it was a traditional apparition called the meddlecat, it was still also Hanekawa Tsubasa herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.28,0:00:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The side of herself she suppressed, who took all the hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.60,0:00:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanekawa Tsubasa’s other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.14,0:00:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If we accept the view that people are flipped, we can apply that to others as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.70,0:01:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Tiny Karen was a novel sight, a true innovation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.76,0:01:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,While to me, it was as shocking as discovering the New World,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.13,0:01:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like Kuchinawa-san said, Karen was conscious of her height,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.03,0:01:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And a gap between her physical and mental growth no doubt existed within her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.37,0:01:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It was always real.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.27,0:01:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If that hidden side of her were given form, it could very well manifest in such manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.13,0:01:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That form was in no way new.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.69,0:01:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the embodiment of her inner unbalance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.77,0:01:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ononoki-chan’s case is something she told me once.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.98,0:01:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They simply don’t appear on the surface; she simply cannot express them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.36,0:01:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But she’s definitely not emotionless or expressionless.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.98,0:01:45.29,Monowall B,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1350,630)\fscx80\fscy80\b1}Koyomi’s ice cream \N– do not eat
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.00,0:01:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, my impression of her wasn’t that her personality had changed, \Nbut that the awfulness of her personality had come to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.36,0:01:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In Hachikuji Mayoi’s case, it’s even simpler to put two and two together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.72,0:02:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, Hachikuji appeared in front of me as a 10-year-old-girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.51,0:02:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,However, even then she was a ghost who’d lost her life 10-odd years before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.01,0:02:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you added everything together, she would be about 21 years old now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.44,0:02:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind the surface of a 10-year-old girl, were the qualities of an adult woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.08,0:02:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ghosts don’t age.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.05,0:02:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The passage of time doesn’t apply to oddities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.69,0:02:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,While we can’t simply calculate her mental age, her history of having wandered around for 11 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.92,0:02:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether she falls to hell or becomes a god, would not disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.28,0:02:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Although I don’t completely understand it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.92,0:02:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,While the likes of Kanbaru who’d fawn over her shouting “little girl, little girl, so cute, co cute” wouldn’t see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.76,0:02:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hachikuji did have such a hidden side.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.95,0:02:50.43,Monowall B,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1080,320)\fscx100\fscy100\b1\fry180}Kitashirahebi\N Shrine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.62,0:02:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If that side of her would be put in front, it might just take that kind of shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.18,0:02:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of Kanbaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.67,0:03:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Her left hand, the monkey’s paw was an artifact that would see the hidden intent behind its owners wish, and grant it accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.84,0:03:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It in itself was an oddity that would turn things inside out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.20,0:03:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What I saw as the Rainy Devil in a raincoat and boots, was the hidden side of Kanbaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.96,0:03:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The affection she feels towards me as her senpai is not a lie, but on the other hand
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.36,0:03:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely getting rid of the Araragi-hatred deep in her is likely impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.08,0:03:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not that it had reappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.97,0:03:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It had always been there, and still is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.47,0:03:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a transformation, just a reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.47,0:03:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It almost sounds like I’m talking mathematics here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.80,0:03:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But to put in in simpler terms, the Rainy Devil was Kanbaru Suruga herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.49,0:03:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of mathematics, let’s talk about poor Oikura Sodachi, who I could barely look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.33,0:03:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,With her unburdened personality I haven’t been shown even a glance of before,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.03,0:03:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way she was fitting in at the Araragi household were, more than I could imagine,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.85,0:03:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A perfect situation she would’ve only dreamed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.68,0:03:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At least, I’d like to think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.64,0:04:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to believe that deep down, Oikura Sodachi wished for such a fictitious happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.89,0:04:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Being able to think that behind her rough attitude and aggressive demeanor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.75,0:04:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There was such a hidden side would bring me some sort of relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.59,0:04:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,While this reading of Oikura Sodachi sounds awfully convenient to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.68,0:04:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I find it impossible to discuss this childhood friend based only on logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.00,0:04:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to that, explaining Sengoku Nadeko’s case is simpler and more convincing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.19,0:04:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuchinawa-san was created by her,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.55,0:04:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As a god native to this land, enshrined at Kitashirahebi shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.98,0:04:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,While not exactly a split personality, Shinobu and I have seen her talking to Kuchinawa-san once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.93,0:04:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu and I could not see this god.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:04:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a snake, nestling in her hidden side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.28,0:05:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That rough way of speaking, slovenly attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.25,0:05:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That was also Sengoku Nadeko.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.83,0:05:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The very same person, as she put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.91,0:05:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no Sengoku Nadeko who’s only docile, quiet, and cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.13,0:05:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind the maturity, childishness. Quiet on surface, outspoken inside. Cheekiness behind the cuteness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.44,0:05:23.49,TV,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1115,860)\fscx300\fscy300\b1\fry180\frz-4\alpha&H90}Onigiri-man
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.59,0:05:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There was always such a Sengoku Nadeko deep down, ready to explode and burst out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.31,0:05:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.76,0:05:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought this world was strange, but upon rereading my adventures so far…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.40,0:05:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out it isn’t that complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.92,0:05:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I was simply seeing their other sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.91,0:05:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In this world, inconsistencies and paradoxes are allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.48,0:05:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But not because it was a mirror world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.19,0:05:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s because these girls were actors originating from the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.45,0:06:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Given freedom of thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.02,0:06:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking about it that way, it’s as if I managed to find a rule grounding this unstable, uncertain world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.69,0:06:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Allowing me to see the scenery where left and right are reversed through a different lens.{\fad(0,500)}
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.01,0:07:18.23,Monowall B,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1100,730)\fscx150\fscy150\b1\fry180\alpha&H55}Clean     Spirit{wasn't it "purity and spirit" in the other gatari shows?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.44,0:07:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.56,0:07:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When she said that she’d reveal her opinion last, she wasn’t bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.75,0:07:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,She had doubts about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.25,0:07:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Still. Let’s put aside whether we’re inside the mirror, in a mirror world, a parallel world or another dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.25,0:07:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s filled with people you know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.52,0:07:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Your family, friends, kouhai, childhood friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.68,0:07:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that’s true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.71,0:07:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Then where are you, Araragi-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.88,0:07:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.48,0:07:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven’t met yourself. Isn’t that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.03,0:07:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, including myself and Kuchinawa-san, knows you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.98,0:07:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We each have some sort of connection to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.11,0:08:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Another Araragi-kun… Your other side… wouldn’t he have to exist here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.31,0:08:08.28,Monowall B,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1100,730)\fscx150\fscy150\b1\fry180\alpha&H55}Clean     Spirit{see other note}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.65,0:08:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Since they all know me, it’d be strange if a me didn’t exist here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.38,0:08:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he’s not here now, he had to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.94,0:08:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My reflection from this morning, who didn’t follow my movements, staring at me with his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.10,0:08:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you switched places, and he’s in your world right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.32,0:08:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he’d be in the same shoes, lost in a world full of inconsistencies he can’t make heads or tails of.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.80,0:08:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If that’s the case, he might be more troubled than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.04,0:08:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If I think this through, based on the examples of Black Hanekawa and Rainy Devil,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.26,0:08:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My other self that should’ve been in this world…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.00,0:08:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Araragi Koyomi… Araragi Koyomi’s other side…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.72,0:08:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Would be my nemesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.32,0:08:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only be Oshino Ougi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.42,0:09:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t you call it a day and rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.76,0:09:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuchinawa-san and I will try to keep looking around, so come back around tomorrow evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.98,0:09:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, if you find a chance to return home before that, don’t let it slip away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.73,0:09:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If that happens, just leave behind a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.93,0:09:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. I’m sorry for all this trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.02,0:09:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it’s no trouble at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.46,0:09:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping peace in this town is my job right now, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.58,0:09:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I am troubled though. Being dragged out of retirement like this…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.38,0:09:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But I suppose I am curious about that cat, so…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.42,0:09:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we prepare for the long haul, I can’t afford to stay long.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.42,0:09:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said before, if I get into university, I’ll have to go and deal with the paperwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.20,0:10:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,After bath, nothing special happened with the mirror. Having confirmed that, I felt dejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.88,0:10:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll just go to sleep…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.04,0:10:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps everything will be solved when I wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.13,0:10:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Koyomi! Dry your hair properly or you’ll catch a cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.12,0:10:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Your shining charms alone won’t do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.85,0:10:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What? What is it? Did I say something bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.08,0:10:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Koyomi, are you angry? Please, don’t act so cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.91,0:10:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get turned on, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.37,0:10:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Oik-…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.29,0:10:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sodachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.44,0:11:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something special you know about mirrors?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something about how mirrors can’t perfectly reflect images…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.31,0:11:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Mirrors work by reflecting light, but they can’t completely reflect all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.42,0:11:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think a normal mirror reflects about 80%.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.52,0:11:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The mirror’s surface will always be somewhat foggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.80,0:11:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reflection seems dimmer than reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.84,0:11:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,While we recognize ourselves in the mirror, we only see ourselves vaguely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.08,0:11:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We can only have a vague understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.40,0:11:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The details become blurry, inaccurate…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.66,0:12:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My sleep was disturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.28,0:12:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sssh. Devilish Onii-chan, get up without making a sound so you don’t wake Sodachi-oneechan up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.99,0:12:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Change your clothes and get ready to go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.08,0:12:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did Ononoki-chan’s emotion-filled, expressive way of talking go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.54,0:12:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay quiet and follow me, Onii-chan. If you do that, I can help you meet Shinobu.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.78,0:12:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, this world’s Kiss-Shot Acerola-Orion Heart-Under-Blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.59,0:12:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me be straight. Don’t expect too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.30,0:12:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m also very far from understanding everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.78,0:12:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ononoki-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.91,0:12:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Onii-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.48,0:12:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Err, well…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.04,0:13:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you’d like an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.55,0:13:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.08,0:13:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what thoughts make you tick. From little girls, to petite girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.60,0:13:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t put me on such a narrow spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.21,0:13:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And those are not thoughts, but tastes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.53,0:13:09.92,Monowall W,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(960,320)\fscx150\fscy150\b1}Thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.33,0:13:10.34,Monowall W,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(960,320)\fscx150\fscy150\b1}Thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.54,0:13:10.88,Monowall W,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(960,320)\fscx150\fscy150\b1}Tastes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.37,0:13:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Not my tastes though!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.77,0:13:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m still a pro, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.32,0:13:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning when you saw me, talked to me, you definitely felt something was amiss with this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.40,0:13:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, I thought there was something amiss with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.50,0:13:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When you stare into the abyss, the abyss stares back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.36,0:13:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s this? How come Onii-chan left without stripping my panties? Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.20,0:13:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those thoughts served as my starting point.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.68,0:13:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn’t you have found a better place to start?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.91,0:13:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you say panties? Underwear? Did you mean to say pants, as in trousers? Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.80,0:13:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows. Put your hand on your heart, and ask yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.37,0:13:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, you didn’t do the usual thing with my chest either. That also tipped me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.90,0:13:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The usual thing with your chest? What’s that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.59,0:14:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the thing I usually do with your chest?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.70,0:14:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m unable to ignore uncertain elements, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.92,0:14:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,After you left, I performed a self-check.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.93,0:14:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I started thinking, why did my behavior surprise you? Why did you force me down?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.82,0:14:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Force you down? I’m sure I didn’t do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.44,0:14:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I meant “why were you freaking out?”. My mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.16,0:14:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s completely different!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.08,0:14:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistake, my foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.13,0:14:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of my maintenance, while I didn’t find out what freaked you out, at the very least
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.43,0:14:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that the way I was, I couldn’t perform at full capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.38,0:14:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That as a being in service of Onee-chan, as her shikigami, I was imperfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.53,0:14:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I reconstructed my personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.48,0:14:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I shook it up. Brushed it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.29,0:15:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Although I couldn’t tell how it turned out, judging by your response, it seems to have mostly gone well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.49,0:15:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it’s nothing worth great praise. It was only possible with your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.16,0:15:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Onii-chan…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.56,0:15:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for not stripping my panties back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.66,0:15:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Please. I simply didn’t do the obvious thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.02,0:15:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I already told you, I don’t fully understand everything either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.60,0:15:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I’m forcing myself a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.88,0:15:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Changing my character this much is already pushing the boundaries of what an oddity is allowed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.70,0:15:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn’t be strange for the darkness to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.56,0:15:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that, there’s a limit to how much I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.43,0:15:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If I get too zealous, I might risk destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.84,0:15:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can’t disappear before we fulfill our promise to see the ocean together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.20,0:15:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I make such a cool promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.83,0:15:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,While stripping her panties every morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.25,0:16:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what happened after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.79,0:16:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like how I went to the Kitashirahebi shrine to ask for advice, did you also start your investigation?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.86,0:16:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So you went to the Kitashirahebi shrine. Hmm. Tell me more about that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.07,0:16:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you weren’t following what I’ve been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.21,0:16:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, don’t expect so much from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.23,0:16:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Forming a new personality was a considerable strain, so my thoughts are all jumbled up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.22,0:16:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I did realize that you were up to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.00,0:16:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought the possibility that you went out to buy a present for Sodachi-oneechan was just as high.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.58,0:16:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(960,885)\fscx200\fscy200\b1\}Exit
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.58,0:16:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did that possibility come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.56,0:16:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,She was pestering you a lot about it, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.12,0:16:47.20,Default,1,0,0,0,,“Koyomi, buy it, please! Pretty please! I won’t let go until you say yes!”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.92,0:16:49.98,Default,1,0,0,0,,She really makes me spoil her, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.00,0:16:50.31,Box,1,0,0,0,,{\p1}m 510 -180 l 1100 -180 1100 400 510 400{\p0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.08,0:16:50.31,Default,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1490,303)\fscx120\fscy120}Talk to her, despite everything
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.16,0:16:50.31,Default,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1284,383)\fscx120\fscy120}Praise her
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.21,0:16:50.31,Default,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1299,464)\fscx120\fscy120}Body Touch
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.25,0:16:50.31,Default,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1224,544)\fscx120\fscy120}Kiss
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.29,0:16:50.31,Default,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1310,623)\fscx120\fscy120}Change area
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.33,0:16:50.31,Default,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1345,705)\fscx120\fscy120}Invite to a hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.41,0:16:50.31,Default,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1223,783)\fscx120\fscy120}Run
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.64,0:16:52.38,Default,1,0,0,0,,What did she even ask for?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.38,0:17:00.76,Default,1,0,0,0,,And while I’d always try stripping your panties, I’d also fulfill a request like that from Oikura?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.76,0:17:03.52,Default,1,0,0,0,,Just what kind of person am I in this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.00,0:17:07.67,Default,1,0,0,0,,Aah, I bet Sodachi-oneechan will be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.99,0:17:10.17,Default,1,0,0,0,,Stop that. Don’t put pressure on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.47,0:17:16.43,Default,1,0,0,0,,Disappointing her is a cruel experience for me. Stop adding to my list of tasks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.92,0:17:22.75,Default,1,0,0,0,,So, after your investigation, you decided to help me and Shinobu meet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.75,0:17:29.40,Default,1,0,0,0,,Exactly. I won’t go into details, because I’m excited to see what kind of face you’ll make,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.40,0:17:37.26,Default,1,0,0,0,,But as you’d expect, that former Kiss-Shot Acerola-Orion Heart-Under-Blade is not the one you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.26,0:17:39.07,Default,1,0,0,0,,Just be ready for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.36,0:17:41.24,Default,1,0,0,0,,Sure, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.24,0:17:43.95,Default,1,0,0,0,,Did you say you’re excited to say what face I’ll make?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:45.96,Default,1,0,0,0,,I did. So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.96,0:17:48.08,Default,1,0,0,0,,That line doesn’t give you a ticket to act cheeky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.61,0:17:51.84,Default,1,0,0,0,,I don’t know what exactly goes on in your world, so…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.65,0:17:57.55,Default,1,0,0,0,,Am I getting along with Onee-chan over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.55,0:18:01.04,Default,1,0,0,0,,Huh? Err, well…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.04,0:18:03.89,Default,1,0,0,0,,Hmm. Well, that’s about what I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.06,0:18:11.06,Default,1,0,0,0,,So, whose panties did you strip today, and where?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.06,0:18:14.69,Default,1,0,0,0,,If you want to know what I did today, you could ask normally.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.24,0:18:19.45,Default,1,0,0,0,,If I recall, you went to Kitashirahebi shrine first, to strip Mayoi-san’s panties.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.45,0:18:20.95,Default,1,0,0,0,,That’s blasphemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.95,0:18:23.20,Default,1,0,0,0,,I’d be struck right then and there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.16,0:18:28.96,Default,1,0,0,0,,After that exchange, I explained the gist of what happened today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.56,0:18:36.96,Default,1,0,0,0,,Uhum. So today,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.96,0:18:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You stripped the panties of Mayoi-san, monkey Onee-chan, cat Onee-chan, snake Onee-chan, and finally Sodachi-oneechan, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.80,0:18:46.48,Default,1,0,0,0,,You’re completely talking in panties now, aren’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.48,0:18:49.73,Default,1,0,0,0,,Oops. I forgot to include the fire sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.73,0:18:51.23,Default,1,0,0,0,,You don’t need to.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.59,0:18:56.74,Default,1,0,0,0,,So amazing, devilish Onii-chan. Your sisters’ panties aren’t even worth mentioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.74,0:19:00.57,Default,1,0,0,0,,Could you be amazed by me in a different way?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.57,0:19:04.93,Default,1,0,0,0,,If that’s the most amazing thing you took away from my story, I’ll be amazingly sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.57,0:19:10.49,Default,1,0,0,0,,Well, how you described everyone is how I always knew them to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.49,0:19:15.88,Default,1,0,0,0,,But there is one point where we are of the same opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.88,0:19:17.63,Default,1,0,0,0,,Oh, what’s that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.63,0:19:20.01,Default,1,0,0,0,,It’s the first time we’re in agreement, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.43,0:19:25.52,Default,1,0,0,0,,Don’t talk like we’re in some buddy cop skit. I’m sure we agreed on things countless times before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.52,0:19:26.26,Default,1,0,0,0,,So, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.73,0:19:30.27,Default,1,0,0,0,,The fact that Black Hanekawa saved you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.27,0:19:35.27,Default,1,0,0,0,,According to what I know about her, that’s completely impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.32,0:19:43.85,Default,1,0,0,0,,Still, I can’t think of anyone who would ask Black Hanekawa to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.85,0:19:48.19,Default,1,0,0,0,,That’s true. I don’t know anyone who would ever help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.68,0:19:50.33,Default,1,0,0,0,,I wouldn’t either, for one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.33,0:19:55.02,Default,1,0,0,0,,That’s not what I meant. I’m talking about who could make that request of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.02,0:19:58.84,Default,1,0,0,0,,And what do you mean that you wouldn’t? Don’t just casually hurt my feelings!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.32,0:20:01.56,Default,1,0,0,0,,Aren’t you helping me right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.56,0:20:06.91,Default,1,0,0,0,,I’m just making you think so, biding my time to see what face you’ll make when it all comes crumbling down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.91,0:20:09.12,Default,1,0,0,0,,I can’t believe what an awful personality you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.12,0:20:12.09,Monowall O,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1560,774)\fscx100\fscy100\b0\}Rainy Devil attacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.25,0:20:12.09,Monowall O,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1614,858)\fscx100\fscy100\b0\}Koyomin took 291 points
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.25,0:20:12.09,Monowall O,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1470,937)\fscx100\fscy100\b0\}of damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.25,0:20:12.09,Monowall O,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1500,1016)\fscx100\fscy100\b0\}Koyomin died!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.22,0:20:12.10,Default,1,0,0,0,,Go back and rebuild it from scratch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.24,0:20:19.65,Default,1,0,0,0,,Does Shinobu know that I’m coming? I won’t pry much if you tell me not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.65,0:20:21.99,Default,1,0,0,0,,But basically, do we have an appointment?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.99,0:20:24.24,Default,1,0,0,0,,We do. No need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.64,0:20:29.86,Default,1,0,0,0,,I’m not sure what it’s like in your world, but here, that vixen and I are best of friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.86,0:20:35.88,Default,1,0,0,0,,It sure doesn’t sound like it. When you call her a vixen, it just oozes malice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.74,0:20:42.16,Monowall G,1,0,0,0,,{sign}{\move(990,30,1000,1230,0,0)\fscx120\fscy120\b0\frz7\fry180}NO ENTRY
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.66,0:20:43.38,Default,1,0,0,0,,Whoa. Now that we’ve come this far, I understood where Ononoki-chan was taking me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.76,0:20:47.64,Default,1,0,0,0,,The derelict building used by the wandering specialist, Oshino meme.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.64,0:20:51.39,Default,1,0,0,0,,Past here are the remains of the former cram school.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.17,0:20:59.36,Default,1,0,0,0,,In the world I know, a fire occurred here last summer. It completely burned down, and nothing was left.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.36,0:21:05.28,Default,1,0,0,0,,But if she’s taking me there, that derelict building might still be intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.84,0:21:16.79,Default,1,0,0,0,,Then in this world, instead of living in my shadow, she might have continued living in that classroom together with Oshino.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.31,0:21:25.22,Default,1,0,0,0,,In that case, I would expect that she’s not too fond of me – of Araragi Koyomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.52,0:21:33.98,Default,1,0,0,0,,With Ononoki-chan around, I suppose my life isn’t in danger, but it might not hurt to be a little more cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.92,0:21:42.45,Default,1,0,0,0,,We arrived at our destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.75,0:22:07.90,Default,1,0,0,0,,Is Shinobu… in here? Does she live in this castle, Ononki-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.90,0:22:13.63,Default,1,0,0,0,,That’s right, devilish Onii-chan. She is right here. She lives here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.85,0:22:16.39,Default,1,0,0,0,,Let’s get inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.39,0:22:19.85,Default,1,0,0,0,,Inside? Uh, can we just enter like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.27,0:22:23.20,Default,1,0,0,0,,Do you think a castle like this would have an intercom?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.12,0:22:27.80,Default,1,0,0,0,,By the way, Ononoki-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.80,0:22:29.82,Default,1,0,0,0,,What is it, devilish Onii-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.82,0:22:34.40,Default,1,0,0,0,,I believed that Shinobu didn’t even exist in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.40,0:22:38.86,Default,1,0,0,0,,That she couldn’t be inside the mirror, since vampires don’t have reflections.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.86,0:22:43.12,Default,1,0,0,0,,That’s one of the inconsistencies of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.12,0:22:47.12,Default,1,0,0,0,,I also call you devilish Onii-chan, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.12,0:22:50.62,Default,1,0,0,0,,Yeah, at one point, you stuck with using that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.06,0:22:53.51,Default,1,0,0,0,,Do you know why I call you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.03,0:22:57.26,Default,1,0,0,0,,Why, well… sure, I understand why.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.26,0:22:59.79,Default,1,0,0,0,,I see. Well, I don’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.89,0:23:02.02,Default,1,0,0,0,,What do you mean…?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.39,0:23:06.65,Default,1,0,0,0,,We’re here. The former Kiss-Shot Acerola-Orion Heart-Under-Blade is waiting for you in this bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.09,0:23:11.91,Default,1,0,0,0,,Although calling her that, or Oshino Shinobu might not be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.94,0:23:16.16,Default,1,0,0,0,,Does that mean that she’s not “former” here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.16,0:23:19.41,Default,1,0,0,0,,Good intuition. There goes one thing to look forward for.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.74,0:23:22.79,Default,1,0,0,0,,Stop enjoying yourself! Don’t look forward to anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.60,0:23:31.04,Default,1,0,0,0,,Hold up, does that mean that her current self, her self in this world hasn’t lost her powers as a vampire?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.04,0:23:33.22,Default,1,0,0,0,,That she’s right in her prime?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.59,0:23:40.19,Default,1,0,0,0,,She’s not the former Kiss-Shot Acerola-Orion Heart-Under-Blade, not Oshino Shinbou…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.19,0:23:43.61,Default,1,0,0,0,,But the real Kiss-Shot Acerola-Orion Heart-Under-Blade?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.58,0:24:05.57,Default,1,0,0,0,,Just by glancing at that silhouette, I understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.57,0:24:08.09,Default,1,0,0,0,,I understood everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.49,0:24:15.28,Default,1,0,0,0,,Welcome to my humble dwelling, Araragi-sama. This would be our first time meeting, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.28,0:24:21.10,Default,1,0,0,0,,My name is Kiss-Shot Acerola-Orion Heart-Under-Blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.42,0:24:27.41,Default,1,0,0,0,,There she was, giving me a peculiar greeting. As beautiful as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.41,0:24:30.99,Default,1,0,0,0,,But this time, not as a vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.54,0:24:33.34,Default,1,0,0,0,,She was a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.34,0:24:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,
